\"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-powered video surveillance technology\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympic Games Law\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On day one, we were accosted by a soldier for filming a sign informing people that they could not proceed past a metal gate to see the Seine River, where the opening ceremony is to be staged.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"a soldier\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"a sign\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 857}, {\"ngram\": \"a metal gate\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is Olympic Paris.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not go to the Seine, but you can have your personal information taken down for publicizing this fact.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0942299594147434e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your personal information\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"this fact\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1103}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French are not passively imbibing the Olympic spectacle.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1110, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9731020808717722, \"rank\": 0.024830221659780435, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spectacle\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tomorrow activists aremobilizingin Place de la R\\u00e9publique to challenge the five-ring juggernaut that has rolled into their city, with groups likeSaccage 2024,Le Revers de La M\\u00e9daille, andExtinction Rebellionout front.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"score\": 0.9919463876317131, \"rank\": 0.007170795306387261, \"text\": \"Place de la R\\u00e9publique\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tomorrow activists\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"the five-ring juggernaut\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"their city\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"groups\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"likeSaccage\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"andExtinction Rebellionout front\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"counter-opening ceremony\\\" promises to raise numerous criticisms of the Olympics, from the displacement of migrants and unhoused people to the fake environmentalism embedded in France's Olympic messaging.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9252580890522655, \"rank\": 0.08077164847943842, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The \\\"counter-opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1414}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous criticisms\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"the displacement\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"the fake environmentalism\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Alauzy, an organizer with Le Revers de La M\\u00e9daille andM\\u00e9decins du Monde, explained to us the philosophy undergirding the mass displacement of poor people that unfolded in the weeks and years before the Paris Olympics: \\\"In Paris, the social cleansing can be understood with a double logic of dispersion: a dispersion within the Olympic's city public space, to avoid tent cities, slums, squats, and disperse the marginalized people, and a dispersion within the whole country, so that to delocalize the unwanted and push the misery away from the Olympic city.\\\"\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 2157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}, {\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paul Alauzy\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"an organizer\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1620}, {\"ngram\": \"andM\\u00e9decins du Monde\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\"